= escape - HTML/URI/shell escaping utilities
<%
  def version
    File.read("VERSION").chomp
  end
%>

escape library provides several HTML/URI/shell escaping functions.

== Author

Tanaka Akira <akr@fsij.org>

== Feature

* several escaping/composing functions
  * HTML text
  * HTML attribute
  * HTML form (x-www-form-urlencoded)
  * URI path
  * shell command line
* non-string-to-string functions for ease real usages and avoid double-escape

== Usage

  require 'escape'

  Escape.shell_command(["echo", "*"]) #=> "echo '*'"
  Escape.uri_path("a?b/c?d/e?f") #=> "a%3Fb/c%3Fd/e%3Ff"
  Escape.html_form([["a","b"], ["c","d"]]) #=> "a=b&c=d"
  Escape.html_form({"a"=>"b", "c"=>"d"}) #=> "a=b&c=d"
  Escape.html_text("a & b < c > d") #=> "a &amp; b &lt; c &gt; d"
  Escape.html_attr("ab&<>\"c") #=> "\"ab&amp;&lt;&gt;&quot;c\""

